                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.08985/2605.08985v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Comparison of high-resolution MLLM encoding paradigms.(a) Previous works feed the full image into the ViT under global encoding and reduce visual tokens only at the post-ViT connector. (b) Our work, LLaVA-UHD v4, adopts slice-based encoding and introduces an intra-ViT compression module𝒟\\mathcal{D}that reduces token count early in the vision encoder.𝒟\\mathcal{D}performs local window attention followed by pixel unshuffle and MLP-based fusion, enabling later layers to operate on fewer tokens. Compared to (a), this design substantially lowers ViT-internal compute, supports more aggressive compression ratios, and incurs nearly no performance loss.",
                "position": 536
            }
